  "response": "No, it will not harm your MacBook Pro to use it while it's fully charged and plugged in. Apple has built-in battery management systems that prevent overcharging and protect the battery's health. Modern MacBooks are designed to stop charging when the battery reaches 100% and will use power directly from the AC adapter while maintaining the battery at an optimal charge level. In fact, Apple recommends keeping your MacBook plugged in when possible to ensure consistent power and performance.",
